(February 9, 1962)

In decisions Nos. 1-13: Present — Bergan, P. J., Coon, Gibson, Herlihy and Taylor, JJ.

(A) In the Matter of the Claim of Minnie Bleich, Respondent, v. 63rd Building Corp. et al., Appellants. Workmen’s Compensation Board, Respondent. (B) Frederick W. Marks, Jr., et al., Appellants, v. Village of Lake Placid et al., Respondents.

[In each action] Motions for permission to reargue or in the alternative to appeal to the Court of Appeals denied, without costs.
